abstract: I couldn’t settle for a yes man, especially a yes man who didn’t appear to read. Could he change?

lead_paragraph: CHRIS was not my type. My type had angular cheekbones, rakishly tousled hair, an impractical liberal arts degree and a misanthropic worldview. My type hungered for atonal music and radical feminist literary theory and anything else you might find on the dusty back shelf of a used bookstore.
